{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"lambswool-shaded-eider","description":"# ACLI bulk-path 429 parity\n\nThe REST helpers honor `Retry-After` + exponential backoff + jitter on 429\n(`acli_subprocess.py:236-292`), but the ACLI-subprocess bulk path (search/create) retries only\ngeneric `CalledProcessError` with fixed delays and does not parse `Retry-After`. Sustained\nrate-limiting on the bulk path is handled more coarsely than the REST path.\n\n## What / files\n- `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/acli_subprocess.py` — bring the bulk-path retry to parity:\n  parse/honor `Retry-After`, exponential backoff + jitter, same retryable set {429,502,503}.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Bulk-path retries honor `Retry-After` on 429 with jittered exponential backoff.\n- [ ] Retryable HTTP set matches the REST path {429,502,503}.\n- [ ] Unit test asserting a 429 on the bulk path backs off and honors Retry-After.\n- [ ] Non-idempotent writes retain the no-blind-retry-on-timeout guard.\n","id":"943f-8303-829b-443a","parent_id":"ace2-f784-4b19-4f22","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Align ACLI bulk-path 429 handling with the REST path (honor Retry-After)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783470421288093001,"uuid":"0523f46d-3490-45b5-9484-f569e9a195f2"}